[coughing continues]

1033
01:06:27.622 --> 01:06:30.157
[whimpering]

1034
01:06:30.190 --> 01:06:31.458
[crying out]

1035
01:06:34.328 --> 01:06:37.064
[coughing]

1036
01:06:47.509 --> 01:06:50.545
Oh, God. [screaming]

1037
01:06:51.411 --> 01:06:54.414
[grunting]

1038
01:06:56.751 --> 01:06:58.786
[struggling]

1039
01:07:04.424 --> 01:07:05.492
[door thuds]

1040
01:07:09.363 --> 01:07:12.767
[grunting]

1041
01:07:15.302 --> 01:07:17.371
[coughing]

1042
01:07:26.246 --> 01:07:27.749
[screaming]

1043
01:07:29.216 --> 01:07:30.284
[Allen screaming]

1044
01:07:30.317 --> 01:07:33.655
[breathing heavily]

1045
01:07:47.635 --> 01:07:49.236
Well, folks.

1046
01:07:49.704 --> 01:07:51.739
I don't think
there's a way out of here.

1047
01:07:52.740 --> 01:07:56.678
[coughing]

1048
01:08:02.382 --> 01:08:04.318
Why am I here?

1049
01:08:04.686 --> 01:08:06.153
You may be asking yourself.

1050
01:08:08.288 --> 01:08:09.791
"How lame is this?"

1051
01:08:09.824 --> 01:08:13.327
This was supposed to be
a story about...

1052
01:08:14.294 --> 01:08:18.265
About a man hunting a monster.

1053
01:08:19.601 --> 01:08:20.835
Instead,

1054
01:08:20.868 --> 01:08:22.637
I'm going to die

1055
01:08:22.670 --> 01:08:25.740
in the escape room
from hell. [chuckling]

1056
01:08:25.773 --> 01:08:28.141
[grunting]

1057
01:08:31.913 --> 01:08:33.280
[indistinct]

1058
01:08:38.653 --> 01:08:40.253
What's the point?

1059
01:08:41.455 --> 01:08:43.625
[coughing & breathing heavily]

1060
01:08:46.961 --> 01:08:50.397
[ominous music playing]

1061
01:08:57.371 --> 01:09:00.508
[moaning in fear]

1062
01:09:02.844 --> 01:09:05.245
No, no. Please.

1063
01:09:05.278 --> 01:09:06.413
Please.

1064
01:09:08.583 --> 01:09:09.784
No!

1065
01:09:10.384 --> 01:09:13.621
[whimpering]

1066
01:09:33.007 --> 01:09:34.374
[paper scraping]

1067
01:09:35.409 --> 01:09:37.578
[paper crinkling]

1068
01:09:39.312 --> 01:09:40.748
[inhaling]

1069
01:09:47.421 --> 01:09:49.891
[Jean]
<i>Keep moving forward, Don.</i>

1070
01:09:49.924 --> 01:09:52.627
<i>Life is crazy.</i>

1071
01:09:52.660 --> 01:09:54.796
<i>But so am I, for you.</i>

1072
01:09:55.930 --> 01:09:57.632
<i>Stay crazy for me.</i>

1073
01:09:58.933 --> 01:10:01.334
<i>Love always, Jean.</i>

1074
01:10:04.772 --> 01:10:06.339
[paper crinkling]

1075
01:10:20.588 --> 01:10:22.824
[door creaking open]

1076
01:10:28.996 --> 01:10:31.532
[objects tinkling softly]

1077
01:10:58.693 --> 01:11:01.662
[panting & groaning]

1078
01:11:17.078 --> 01:11:20.047
[Don] <i>Six, find the</i>
<i>encore button in the garage.</i>

1079
01:11:21.749 --> 01:11:24.652
<i>Bait and the other shit,
rigged to explode.</i>

1080
01:11:25.119 --> 01:11:27.989
[Allen panting]

1081
01:11:36.631 --> 01:11:37.698
Shit.

1082
01:11:41.702 --> 01:11:42.770
Shit!

1083
01:11:48.509 --> 01:11:50.511
[groaning]

1084
01:11:51.813 --> 01:11:53.446
[objects tinkling]

1085
01:12:11.933 --> 01:12:15.937
[eerie music playing]

1086
01:12:24.178 --> 01:12:26.681
[faint clattering]

1087
01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:49.003
[music intensifies]

1088
01:13:06.954 --> 01:13:08.488
[clearing throat]

1089
01:13:12.560 --> 01:13:13.728
Ugh. Gross.

1090
01:13:18.766 --> 01:13:20.467
[whimpering]

1091
01:13:23.938 --> 01:13:25.139
How do I even...

1092
01:13:27.174 --> 01:13:28.408
begin...

1093
01:13:29.476 --> 01:13:30.878
to describe what just happened?

1094
01:13:43.024 --> 01:13:44.191
[Allen grunting]

1095
01:13:46.093 --> 01:13:49.764
[ominous music playing]

1096
01:13:51.933 --> 01:13:55.002
[music intensifies]

1097
01:14:23.097 --> 01:14:25.633
[music fades]

1098
01:14:25.666 --> 01:14:27.201
[birds chirping]

1099
01:14:57.198 --> 01:14:58.866
[Allen grunting]

1100
01:15:00.835 --> 01:15:02.036
[exhaling]

1101
01:15:40.274 --> 01:15:41.609
[car door slamming]

1102
01:15:52.186 --> 01:15:53.687
[glove compartment clanks open]

1103
01:15:58.859 --> 01:16:02.563
[somber music starts]

1104
01:16:29.223 --> 01:16:33.627
[music continues]

1105
01:16:56.984 --> 01:16:58.052
Bye, Don.

1106
01:16:58.085 --> 01:17:03.124
♪

1107
01:17:49.803 --> 01:17:51.772
[music fades]

1108
01:17:56.277 --> 01:17:57.344
I'm confused.

1109
01:17:58.345 --> 01:18:00.414
We're having a hard time
following your story.

1110
01:18:01.916 --> 01:18:03.884
You said that you were
interviewing Mr. Thomas

1111
01:18:03.918 --> 01:18:04.985
for a podcast.

1112
01:18:05.019 --> 01:18:06.220
What about?

1113
01:18:12.826 --> 01:18:14.061
I don't know anymore.

1114
01:18:24.939 --> 01:18:27.041
[atmospheric music starts]

1115
01:18:53.133 --> 01:18:56.170
[music continues]

1116
01:19:12.253 --> 01:19:13.887
[Kim] I have no idea
where Allen went.

1117
01:19:13.921 --> 01:19:15.641
It's like he fell off
the face of the earth.

1118
01:19:18.292 --> 01:19:19.360
Yeah, I know.

1119
01:19:22.463 --> 01:19:23.531
Hey, hold on one second.

1120
01:19:30.504 --> 01:19:32.806
Oh, my God.

1121
01:19:34.108 --> 01:19:37.011
[Don] <i>Still</i>
<i>haven't found number 52.</i>

1122
01:19:39.079 --> 01:19:41.282
<i>I see these boxes
scattered around.</i>

1123
01:19:42.916 --> 01:19:44.885
<i>It's kind of like
Jean is watching me.</i>

1124
01:19:47.054 --> 01:19:48.889
<i>The second thing
you need to know</i>

1125
01:19:48.922 --> 01:19:52.993
<i>is that this entire place
is booby trapped.</i>

1126
01:19:53.027 --> 01:19:54.387
[Kim] <i>They loved</i>
<i>your story, Allen.</i>

1127
01:19:56.564 --> 01:19:58.299
- Are you serious?
- Yeah.

1128
01:19:58.966 --> 01:20:00.467
I loved your story.

1129
01:20:00.501 --> 01:20:05.205
It's got so much heart
and suspense.

1130
01:20:06.140 --> 01:20:08.075
It's a survival story,
people love that.

1131
01:20:09.644 --> 01:20:11.221
It's got a bit of everything,
doesn't it?

1132
01:20:11.245 --> 01:20:12.313
Yeah.

1133
01:20:13.280 --> 01:20:14.348
It was a bitch to get.

1134
01:20:15.282 --> 01:20:16.317
Yeah, I bet.

1135
01:20:17.418 --> 01:20:21.055
So listen, APR wants you back.

1136
01:20:21.455 --> 01:20:22.524
Oh, I don't know.

1137
01:20:24.526 --> 01:20:26.026
I mean, what about the lawsuit?

1138
01:20:26.060 --> 01:20:27.595
I have a meeting

1139
01:20:27.629 --> 01:20:29.997
with the board of directors
at APR in the morning,

1140
01:20:30.030 --> 01:20:34.101
but word is that the case
is not going anywhere.

1141
01:20:35.469 --> 01:20:36.538
[Allen sighing]

1142
01:20:37.639 --> 01:20:39.139
They really
want you back, Allen.

1143
01:20:42.176 --> 01:20:44.345
They did have one note
for the story.

1144
01:20:46.146 --> 01:20:47.247
What?

1145
01:20:48.015 --> 01:20:49.116
We never see the monster.

1146
01:20:50.317 --> 01:20:52.219
And? It's a podcast.

1147
01:20:52.252 --> 01:20:55.289
I know that, but...
maybe we do, like,

1148
01:20:55.322 --> 01:20:58.025
a video and get somebody
to animate your story.

1149
01:20:58.058 --> 01:21:00.562
I just... I feel like people
are going to be disappointed

1150
01:21:00.595 --> 01:21:03.030
if they don't get
an image of the monster.

1151
01:21:03.063 --> 01:21:06.568
I mean, you did see it, right?

1152
01:21:07.334 --> 01:21:09.604
I mean, the focus
of the story is Don, isn't it?

1153
01:21:10.605 --> 01:21:12.005
Does the monster even matter?

1154
01:21:12.039 --> 01:21:14.408
[laughs] Yes, Allen, it does.

1155
01:21:14.441 --> 01:21:16.143
Of course it matters,
it's a monster story.

1156
01:21:16.176 --> 01:21:18.096
You can't have a monster story
without a monster.

1157
01:21:22.015 --> 01:21:23.083
Let me think about it.

1158
01:21:24.385 --> 01:21:26.588
- I'll get back to you.
- Awesome.

1159
01:21:28.122 --> 01:21:29.189
Welcome back, Allen.

1160
01:21:31.325 --> 01:21:33.285
Can't wait to see what
your next story's gonna be.

1161
01:21:34.395 --> 01:21:37.364
Hey. Also, I'm curious,

1162
01:21:37.398 --> 01:21:39.066
this monster
with all the eyes...

1163
01:21:40.300 --> 01:21:43.404
do you think there's more
in the woods near Don's house?

1164
01:21:48.743 --> 01:21:52.312
For Don's sake,
I really hope so.

1165
01:21:53.548 --> 01:21:55.015
[chuckles softly]

1166
01:22:05.760 --> 01:22:10.565
[upbeat electronic a starts]

1167
01:22:26.180 --> 01:22:27.981
[announcer] <i>This is</i> U.S. Sane.

1168
01:22:31.519 --> 01:22:32.687
Whenever you're ready.

1169
01:22:51.573 --> 01:22:53.006
I'm not ready.

1170
01:22:57.712 --> 01:22:59.480
I have an amazing
story, but I'm not...

1171
01:23:00.648 --> 01:23:01.716
ready to tell it.

1172
01:23:03.818 --> 01:23:07.187
[inhaling]
Life is complicated.

1173
01:23:10.157 --> 01:23:12.092
People... people are complicated.

1174
01:23:15.429 --> 01:23:18.065
You don't need a podcast host
to tell you that.

1175
01:23:21.134 --> 01:23:23.070
People are always
trying to find...

1176
01:23:24.404 --> 01:23:27.609
a meaning
in life's complications.

1177
01:23:28.676 --> 01:23:30.077
Even when that meaning is...

1178
01:23:31.746 --> 01:23:33.380
Even when that meaning
makes no sense.

1179
01:23:35.583 --> 01:23:37.619
Sometimes crazy things happen.

1180
01:23:38.753 --> 01:23:41.589
And they add up,
and they add up,

1181
01:23:41.623 --> 01:23:44.659
and add up, and the meaning...

1182
01:23:46.794 --> 01:23:48.061
is nothing.

1183
01:23:51.198 --> 01:23:52.366
That's okay,

1184
01:23:53.568 --> 01:23:56.671
because eventually the meaning
will rise to the surface.

1185
01:23:58.372 --> 01:24:00.340
Maybe not in a clear,
decoded way,

1186
01:24:03.210 --> 01:24:04.411
but it will.

1187
01:24:05.580 --> 01:24:07.180
In the meantime...

1188
01:24:08.315 --> 01:24:10.552
let me tell you
the important facts,

1189
01:24:13.521 --> 01:24:15.322
and together
we'll find the story.

1190
01:24:18.225 --> 01:24:19.293
Let me begin...

1191
01:24:21.796 --> 01:24:23.397
with a free-spirited...

1192
01:24:24.398 --> 01:24:28.570
and unpredictable man
named Don Thomas...

1193
01:24:29.804 --> 01:24:31.071
and...

1194
01:24:32.339 --> 01:24:33.608
his wife Jean.

1195
01:24:34.909 --> 01:24:36.243
Who kept him grounded.

1196
01:24:36.276 --> 01:24:40.414
♪

1197
01:24:44.184 --> 01:24:51.826
♪